OL,3,CChief fire officer allowed back to
OL,4,Cwork after investigation into sexist
OL,5,Cmessages
OL,7,FChief Fire Officer of Shropshire Fire
OL,8,FService has been welcomed back to
OL,9,Fwork, despite being found to have
OL,10,Fbehaved inappropriately in relation to
OL,11,Ffemale colleagues.
OL,13,FSimon Hardiman was investigated by the
OL,14,FShropshire Fire Authority, following a
OL,15,Freport from ITV News earlier this year
OL,16,Fwhich revealed derogatory messages
OL,17,Fsent by Mr Hardiman and his Assistant
OL,18,FChief Fire Officer, Adam Matthews.
